The following will be practiced to:
1. Perceive the development process of the body's physical expression.
2. Create and hold dynamics in movement.
3. Focus on every single dance element separately and to integrate it with the whole movement.
4. Save kinetic energy in different motion qualities.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to acquire contemporary dance techniques, which will open up the potential of individual bodies in danceart. To explore innovative opportunities and experiments in movement. At the same time, drawing attention to the understanding of contemporary processes in danceart and bodily perception of these processes in dynamics.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. Student acquires contemporary dance techniques based on body sensational skills, which is the basis of their personal language of movement. 2. Student is aware of optimal use of the body while moving. 3. Student understands contemporary processes in dance and is able to apprehend these processes in dynamics.
